# 6. 羽根つきバトル！

MEIKO: Hello, everyone! Here's the special New Year's menu.
Miku: Oh, red bean soup with red and white dango, and amazake smoothies! Also, a matcha latte with flowers on the dango.
Miku: Your special menu is so extravagant! I don't know what to pick...
Len: Yeah! I want to try everything!
Rin: I've been looking forward to your special menu, MEIKO!
MEIKO: Hehe, I went to town on this one. Order anything you like!
Rin: Okay! Len, what are you getting?
Rin: Or how about we order everything from the New Year's menu one by one and share them all?
Len: Yeah, let's do that! I'll have the matcha latte then!
Rin: And I'll have the red bean soup!
MEIKO: One matcha latte and one red bean soup. Got it.
Miku: For my first order of the year, I'd like a cup of your original house blend, MEIKO.
MEIKO: Hehe, sure.
Miku: Hanging out with everyone and just enjoying a relaxing day really is the best part of New Year's...
MEIKO: Yes. It is very nice, but don't get too lazy!
Len: Yeah, we probably should find a way to work off all of this food...
Rin: Want to go jogging with me after this?
Len: Jogging? But just running is so boring.
Rin: Aww... Fine, what do you want to do?
MEIKO: Oh, more customers...?
An: Hey, MEIKO! Happy New Year!
MEIKO: And Happy New Year to you too, An.
Kohane: Wow, everyone's here today! Happy New Year!
Miku: Happy New Year!
Len: Hey, Akito and Toya are here too! Happy New Year!
Akito: Happy New Year. Thanks for all the help this past year.
Toya: Let's find the time to sing together again too.
Rin: Yeah, of course! We're looking forward to it!
An: What's everyone up to right now?
Miku: Just making the most of our New Year's in a really relaxed fashion.
Kohane: Hehe, that's the best way to spend it!
Rin: Len and I were also talking about finding a way to burn off all the calories from MEIKO's extravagant menu too.
An: Well, if you want to do that, I've got just the thing! Wanna try it?
MEIKO: Oh, Hanetsuki paddles!
Rin: Wait, what are those for...?
MEIKO: They're special paddles used as a New Year's decorations. Supposedly, they bring you good health for the entire year.
Len: Oh, okay...!
Kohane: And you can play a game with them too.
An: You use the paddles like rackets to bounce a shuttlecock back and forth. The player that misses it loses...!
Rin: So it's a Hanetsuki battle! That sounds really fun!
Len: Count me in too!
MEIKO: This game's also supposed to ward off misfortune, so why not play doubles since you brought four rackets?
Toya: But there's one thing that hasn't been mentioned. The loser gets their face painted with ink, so you want to be careful not to get all graffitied.
Akito: Can't they just leave that part out...?
Len: Then we just have to win, right? Don't worry, we've got this!
Rin: That's right! Len and I make the perfect team, so we'll definitely win♪
An: Then Kohane and I will play against you. The winners can scribble whatever they like on the loser's faces just as an added incentive!
Kohane: Wait, An...! Really?!
An: Don't worry, Kohane! We're an unbeatable team!
Rin: Says YOU!
Len: How about you, Akito? Toya?
Toya: I've never actually played Hanetsuki before... Have you, Akito?
Akito: Only once when I was a little kid. I'm happy just watching.
An: You guys are no fun! We're gonna have a blast without them in that case!
Rin: Yeah! Let's go outside!
Miku: I'd like to see this too.
MEIKO: In that case, I'll get your orders ready and keep them in the back until you're done.
Rin: Cool, thanks! Let's go, guys!
Len: We've gotta win, Rin!
Rin: Yeah, we'll win and prove to the world that we're the best team ever!
An: Hehe, look at how cocky they are! Let's show them who's boss, Kohane!
Kohane: Yeah! Let's play our best!
Toya: We'll just watch from here then...
Akito: Wait, what about practice? Sigh... I guess we can do that later since it's New Year's and all...
Miku: Are you ready to begin? I'll be the referee!
Miku: You score one point if your opponents fail to hit the shuttlecock.
Miku: The first to five will be the winner. Is that okay with everybody?
Len: Yeah, sounds good!
An: Same here!
Miku: Okay. Let's start the Hanetsuki Battle!
An: Here goes! Haaah!
Rin: Len, it's on your side!
Len: I've got this... Huh? I missed...?!
An: Nice! That's one point for us!
Kohane: These paddles have a strange shape, so it's not easy to hit the shuttlecock with them.
An: Well, that's unfortunate for Len! Guess what comes next...!
Len: Y-Yeah! Come on then, paint my face already...
Rin: An, can you paint my face too?
Rin: Len and I are a team, so I think it's only fair we get the same treatment!
Miku: Hehe, you're really two peas in a pod.
An: Okay then....! I can do the same thing for both of you.
An: Just a little dab here, and done! Okay, your turn, Rin...
Rin: Eek, it tickles! This is fun! I kinda like it!
Len: Haha! Okay, time to get serious and score some points for our team!
An: Kohane, get it!
Kohane: Yeah! Got it...!
Rin: Oh no! A drop shot...! I won't reach it...!
Rin: But I have to make it! Gooo!
Len: You got it! Nice one, Rin!
Kohane: That was awesome, Rin!
An: My turn, huh? You're next, Len!
Len: Alright, I'm ready!
Len: (If Rin can pull that off, so can I!)
An: There!
Len: I'm on it! Yeah!!!
Kohane: Huh?!
An: Whaaat?! I was sure Len would miss that!
Rin: Good job, Len! We scored a point!
Len: Yeah! Let's keep this up!
Kohane: I-I'm sorry, An! It took me by surprise...
An: That's all good. We'll get back at them!
Miku: This should get interesting.
Len: Bring it on, ladies! You can't beat me and Rin!
An: You're going to regret asking for it, Len!
An: Here you go!!
Len: Hehe, I saw that one coming! Got it!!
